sequenceDiagram
    actor H as Human
    participant B as /build
    participant KB as docs/kanban.md
    participant Code as Codebase
    participant Cfg as Company Config

    H->>B: /build

    note over B: Pre-flight checks
    B->>KB: Read sprint tickets
    B->>Code: Read PRD + testplan
    B->>Cfg: Read ai_human_signoff_required + ai_data_restrictions
    B->>Cfg: Check required tools
    alt Required tools missing
        B->>H: ⛔ Install missing tools — run /tool-check
    end

    alt Buffer window active
        B->>H: ⚠️ Buffer window — BUILD-FEATURES / BUILD-FIXES / STOP
        H->>B: Decision
    end

    B->>Code: Run pre-build health check
    alt Health check fails
        B->>H: ⛔ Codebase broken — fix before /build
    end

    B->>H: Present build queue (AFK + HITL + blocked tickets)
    H->>B: CONFIRM

    loop Each AFK ticket in queue
        B->>H: ⚠️ Smart Zone check — over 100k tokens? (1: /break-down  2: proceed)
        B->>KB: Mark ticket In Progress [>]

        note over B,Code: TDD cycle
        B->>Code: RED — write failing test for behaviour
        B->>Code: GREEN — implement minimum to pass
        B->>Code: REFACTOR — clean up, confirm tests still green

        B->>Code: Lightweight PII hint scan on files written
        alt PII hint found
            B->>H: ⚠️ Possible PII at [file:line] — review before committing
        end

        alt ai_human_signoff_required: true
            B->>H: ✋ AI policy — type APPROVED to close ticket
            H->>B: APPROVED
        end

        B->>KB: Mark ticket Done [x] ✓

        alt Every 3 completed tickets AND 3+ remain
            B->>H: Checkpoint — CONTINUE / PAUSE
            H->>B: Decision
        end
    end

    alt HITL ticket in queue
        B->>H: ⏸ HITL — complete task + type CONTINUE
        H->>B: CONTINUE
    end

    alt Ticket fails twice
        B-->>H: Auto-trigger /diagnose
    end

    B->>H: Build summary (✅ completed / ⏸ HITL stops / 🚧 blocked)
    B->>Code: Record per-ticket actual token bands in kanban-archive.md
